	<purpose>
		This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module to support the requirement to define a boundary representation solid with explicit topology and elementary or free-form geometry. It specializes the generic constructs from ISO 10303-42 for the definition of manifold solid boundary representation models to ensure that such models are completely and unambiguously defined. The faces of the B-rep models defined in this module use the advanced face definition from ISO 10303-1511.
	</purpose>
